BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mSFMeumZPjIWp5sBfZ7wN
SUMMARY:Meet the Artists of Flight Patterns
DTSTAMP:20260410T044138Z
DTSTART:20260415T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Lynnwood Event Center at The District warmly invites you to
	 our spring “Meet the Artists” Reception\, an evening showcasing our lates
	t art exhibit\, “Flight Patterns: The Art & Motion of Winged Life.” Taking
	 place on Tuesday\, April 14th from 6-8pm at the Lynnwood Event Center\, t
	his is a free and fun community event not to be missed! \n\nGuests can mee
	t and mingle with our talented artists and fellow art enthusiasts while en
	joying live music\, complimentary small bites\, and refreshments from the 
	bar. A highlight of the evening will be a live\, participatory installatio
	n by Alexandra Nason\, who will invite guests to decorate individual alumi
	num butterflies that come together as an evolving work of art. Some artist
	s will also speak and answer questions throughout the evening about their 
	work and creative process. \n\nFlight Patterns: The Art & Motion of Winged
	 Life brings together a dynamic collection of works inspired by birds\, fl
	ight\, and the natural rhythms of movement and migration. Through a wide r
	ange of mediums and perspectives\, the exhibit explores the beauty\, symbo
	lism\, and energy of winged life. We hope you’ll join us for an evening of
	 art\, conversation\, and discovery! \n\nThe event is free with RSVP.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/meet-the-artists-of-flight-pa
	tterns/18547110/2026-04-14T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/meet-the-artists-of-fligh
	t-patterns/18547110/2026-04-14T00
LOCATION:Lynnwood Event Center\, 3711 196th Street SW\, Lynnwood\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
