DTSTAMP:20260410T044140Z
DTSTART:20260423T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Interested in expanding your business and need to know more abo
	ut permitting? Have feedback on recent City programming? Want to get more 
	involved in your community and network with your peers? This event is for 
	you!  Representatives from Issaquah Parks\, Human Services\, Sustainabilit
	y\, Environment\, Emergency Management\, and Community Planning and Develo
	pment will be available for questions and conversation.  RSVPs are optiona
	l but highly encouraged: bit.ly/SpringBusinessOpenHouse Event agenda 9 a.m
	. - Event opens\, networking and mingling begins 9:30 a.m. - Mayor Mullet’
	s remarks 9:45-11 a.m. - Open House format for networking or staff questio
	ns\, including the mayor. Short on time? Attendees are free to arrive late
	 and leave early at their convenience!  There is ample street parking arou
	nd Blakely Hall on Northeast Park Drive\, including the Village Green Circ
	le\, and on 25th and 30th Avenues \\(and adjacent side streets\\).  Questi
	ons? Contact economicdevelopment@issaquahwa.gov. We hope to see you there!
	\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/spring-business-open-hou
	se/18529113/2026-04-23T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
